      <h1>New in Version 2.1 - 2004-09-02</h1>
      <ul>
        <li>New configuration option to disable the "Link To" prefix in newly created links.</li>
        <li>IconOverlays now disabled for remote- and floppy drives (speed issues) - thanks to Luke Hamburg and Jan Peter Stotz.</li>
        <li>Version Information included in ntfslink.dll</li>
        <li>"Open Target Folder" in junction context menu now supports <em>\Volume{GUID}</em>-style links. (thanks to Max Kanzler)</li>
        <li>Comes with FAQ.</li>
      </ul>

      <h1>New in Version 2.0 - 2004-08-13</h1>
      <ul>
        <li>Internationalization: The GUI of NTFS Link is now fully localizable.</li>
        <li>
          Drag&Drop menu item now differing clearly between <em>junctions</em> and
          <em>hard links</em>.
        </li>
        <li>
          Drag&Drop menu item hidden, if link creation clearly is not possible (e.g., hard links
          across different file systems).
        </li>
        <li>Alternative way to create links, through the Shell "<em>New</em>" menu.</li>
        <li>Integration in Context Menu of empty directories and junctions.</li>
        <li>Icon Overlays for junction points and hard links.</li>
        <li>Junctions can now be safely deleted from within Windows Explorer.</li>
        <li>
          Moving a junction from within Windows Explorer will now only move the junction itself,
          not the contents of the linked directory.
        </li>
        <li>
          When a junction is copied from within Windows Explorer, NTFS Link will ask the user whether
          he wants to copy the junction itself or the contents of the linked directory.
        </li>
        <li>
          When a folder is deleted, to which junctions are pointing, a warning dialog will be shown.
        </li>
        <li>Added a bunch of glyphs to all the menu items.</li>
        <li>New Configuration-Utility.</li>
      </ul>

